         <abstract>
            <p>Several new algorithms for generating deviates from the $t$ family for the degrees of freedom parameter $\geqslant 1$ are presented. Both acceptance-rejection and probability mixing procedures are developed. The new algorithms outperform traditional methods for generating deviates from the $t$ family. Recommendations are made concerning choosing an algorithm suited to its application.</p>
